<faculty_text>Members of the Department</faculty_text>
<description>Time critically shapes our perceptual experience, yet how the brain represents time is poorly understood. This course investigates the experience of time from multiple perspectives, focusing on a systems-level analysis of visual time perception. Topics include illusions of time, neuronal mechanisms of time, the meaning of timescales, models of time perception, and the influence of expectation on brain activity.</description>
<prerequisites>LS 1a, MCB 80, and permission of the instructor.</prerequisites>
